{SECT 0 {PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 26 "  Elementary Number Theory" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 313 "Save you
r current worksheet as number02.mws.  Remember to save frequently in c
ase of system shut downs in the middle of a work session! In the text \+
mode (click on the cap T button) place your name(s) and date at the to
p of your worksheet.  At the end of this session you will print out an
d turn in your worksheet." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 255 "We continue by experimenting with some more very \+
basic calculations.  Again the intent is to learn some basic MAPLE syn
tax, while observing more neat features of a Computer Algebra System (
CAS).  We will also review some basic concepts from number theory." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 200 "Preform \+
the following calculations with MAPLE.  As you do these exercises ente
r notes and comments onto your worksheet in text mode. As always quest
ions/comments in bold face require written response." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "gcd(6,8);" "
6#-%$gcdG6$\"\"'\"\")" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "1.  " }{TEXT 
257 31 "What is gcd an abreviation for?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "lcm(6,8);" "6#-%$lcmG6$\"
\"'\"\")" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "2.  " }{TEXT 258 31 "What is \+
lcm an abreviation for?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "3.  Compute gcd(6,8)lcm(6,8)." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 "Execute the f
ollowing command sequence:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "
gcd(140,958);" "6#-%$gcdG6$\"$S\"\"$e*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "lcm(140,958);" "6#-%$lcmG6$\"$S\"\"$e*" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 5 "%*%%;" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "140*958;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 " 4.   " }
{TEXT 259 59 "What general formula is suggested by these calculations?
   " }{TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 55 "Test the formula with several more pairs of integers.  \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 24 " Execute the following:." }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "gcd(101
